BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17
18
SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
18
19
codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
19
20
This act shall be known and may be cited as the “Oklahoma Dream
20
21
Accounts Investment Program Act”.
21
22
SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
22
23
in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 9011.1 of Title 62, unless there
23
24
is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
24
Req. No. 3132 Page 1

1
A. As used in this section:
1
2
1. “Trump Account” means a federally authorized Trump Account
2
3
established pursuant to 26 U.S.C., Section 530A;
3
4
2. “Eligible child” means a person who:
4
5
a. is under eighteen (18) years of age at the time the
5
6
application for a Trump Account is submitted,
6
7
b. is a citizen of the United States and is assigned a
7
8
valid Social Security number,
8
9
c. has a primary residence within this state, and
9
10
d. has an established Trump Account; and
10
11
3. “Program” means the Oklahoma Dream Account Investment
11
12
Program.
12
13
B. There is hereby created the Oklahoma Dream Account
13
14
Investment Program, to be administered by the State Treasurer.
14
15
C. The program shall authorize a one-time contribution by this
15
16
state into a Trump Account established for an eligible child,
16
17
subject to the availability of funds.
17
18
D. The State Treasurer is authorized to contribute to Trump
18
19
Accounts upon verification that the Trump Account is established for
19
20
an eligible child and that the contribution does not cause the
20
21
balance of the fund to exceed any applicable federal contribution
21
22
limitations. Upon verification, the State Treasurer shall make a
22
23
one-time deposit of Two Hundred Fifty Dollars ($250.00), as funds
23
24
become available in the Oklahoma Trump Account Investment Fund,
24
Req. No. 3132 Page 2

1
created pursuant to Section 3 of this act. The State Treasurer
1
2
shall make contributions, in the order that verified applications
2
3
are submitted.
3
4
E. Applications for the contribution shall be made on a form
4
5
prescribed by the State Treasurer. The State Treasurer may
5
6
promulgate rules to effectuate the provisions of this section.
6
7
F. Nothing in this act shall be construed to authorize a
7
8
contribution that is prohibited by federal laws or regulations.
8
9
SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
9
10
in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 9011.2 of Title 62, unless there
10
11
is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
11
12
There is hereby created in the State Treasury a revolving fund
12
13
for the State Treasurer to be designated the “Oklahoma Trump Account
13
14
Investment Fund”. The fund shall be a continuing fund, not subject
14
15
to fiscal year limitations, and shall consist of all monies received
15
16
by the State Treasurer that are designated for deposit in the fund.
16
17
All monies accruing to the credit of the fund are hereby
17
18
appropriated and may be budgeted and expended by the State Treasurer
18
19
for the purpose provided for in Section 2 of this act. Expenditures
19
20
from the fund shall be made upon warrants issued by the State
20
21
Treasurer against claims filed as prescribed by law with the
21
22
Director of the Office of Management and Enterprise Services for
22
23
approval and payment.
23
24
SECTION 4. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
24
